{"word":"ἄκανθα","slug":"ἄκανθα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄκανθα</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ἀκή</el> I\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a thorn, prickle</i>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a prickly plant, thistle</i>; in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <i>thistledown</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>:—also <i>a kind of acacia</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>the backbone</i> or <i>spine</i> of animals, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <el>ἄκανθαι</el>, <i>thorny</i> questions, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}